                            <comment id="13072869" author="arulck" created="Fri, 29 Jul 2011 15:42:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to fix the ConcurrentModificationException from SolrDocument&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13073104" author="hossman" created="Sat, 30 Jul 2011 01:32:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Arul: thank you so much for reporting this and especially for submitting a patch with tests!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe the behavior of SolrDocument.getFieldNames is intentional (it&apos;s really just a historical alias for keySet from before that class implemented Map) and the true bug is in the code in BinaryResponseWrriter (recently changed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1566&quot; title=&quot;Allow components to add fields to outgoing documents&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1566&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1566&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached a patch that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;changed your test to use an actual Resolver instance and moved it to TestBinaryResponseWriter&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fixes BinaryResponseWriter.Resolver to use the iterator to remove fields.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adds some javadocs to SolrDocument.getFieldNames clarifying that the Collection is backed by the Map.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13073645" author="hossman" created="Mon, 1 Aug 2011 18:22:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1152885.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CHANGES.txt attrib added to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1566&quot; title=&quot;Allow components to add fields to outgoing documents&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1566&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1566&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; since this was a bug in unreleased code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Arul!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
